msgid ""
"The platform stores Users’ passwords hashed with a random 128 bit salt, "
"unique for each user."
msgstr ""

#: ../../security/ApplicationSecurity.rst:45
msgid ""
"Passwords are hashed using `Argon2 "
"<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Argon2>`_, a key derivation function that "
"was selected as the winner of the `Password Hashing Competition "
"<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Password_Hashing_Competition>`_ in July "
"2015."
msgstr ""

#: ../../security/ApplicationSecurity.rst:47
msgid ""
"The hash involves a per-user salt for each user and a per-system salt for"
" whistleblowers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../security/ApplicationSecurity.rst:50
msgid "Password Complexity"
msgstr ""

#: ../../security/ApplicationSecurity.rst:51
msgid ""
"The system enforces the usage of complex password by implementing a "
"custom algorithm necessary for ensuring a reasonable entropy of each "
"authentication secret."
msgstr ""

